<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>todo list</title>
  <link rel="icon" href="images/favicon.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.0.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm" crossorigin="anonymous">

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&family=Cabin:ital@1&family=Fredoka+One&family=Montserrat&family=Orelega+One&family=Pacifico&family=Rubik+Moonrocks&family=Rubik:wght@800&family=Square+Peg&family=Ubuntu:wght@500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12">
        <div class="box" id="heading2">
          <h2>Last Minute Check Points</h2>
        </div>

        <p class="intro">Meeting presentations, Interviews, Exams, Travel etc are some of the activities that we plan a lot about, but still require something called "Last Minute Check Points" to ensure that whatever we have prepared goes as planned. This can be
          easily achieved by having a small checklist where we can put all the points we think are essential.</p>
        <p class="intro">On this page, you can see a Checklist wherein you can put all the "Last minute checkpoints".</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12">
        <div class="box" id="heading1">
          <h1> <%=kindOfDay%> </h1>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <% for(var i=0 ; i<newItemList.length; i++){ %>
          <div class="item">
            <input type="checkbox">
            <p><%=newItemList[i]%></p>
          </div>
          <%}%>
          <form class="item" action="/" method="post">
            <input type="text" name="newItem" placeholder="New item" autocomplete="off">
            <button type="submit" name="button">+</button>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


  </body>
</html>
